hints_latex:
The mean of a random variable \emph{X} with probability density function
\emph{f(x)} is given by

\begin{align*}
\int_{-\infty}^\infty xf(x)\,dx.
\end{align*}

Once your integration by parts is all done you should find the integral

\begin{align*}
\int_0^{5\pi} \sin^3\left(\frac{x}{10}\right)\,dx
\end{align*}

Use the trigonometric Pythagoras to solve this integral and finish the
problem.

statement_latex:
The length of time in minutes it takes students to solve a certain
mathematics problem (on probability) is a continuous random variable
whose probability density function is

\begin{align*}
f(x) = \begin{cases} k\cos(x/10)\sin^2(x/10), & \text{if } 0 \leq x \leq 5\pi, \\
0, & \text{otherwise.} \end{cases}
\end{align*}

(c) Compute the mean length of time required to solve the problem.
